  "title": "Algebraic models for the aggregation of area features based upon morphological operators",
  "abstract": "Abstract Generalization is a fundamental function in GIS. It has been an important research theme for many years in cartography and GIS. A number of generalization operations have been identified, however most of them, especially those rule-based operations, remain at the conceptual level. This paper describes a set of mathematical (algebraic) models for area aggregation based on the operators developed in mathematical morphology. In this paper, the process of area aggregation is decomposed into two components, viz., combination and shape refinement, and algebraic models for both components are developed. These are demonstrated using various examples. The models provide a mathematical basis for area aggregation in digital generalization of map and other spatial data. The results show that these algebraic models have the potential for successful application.",
